File: Enock Mpianzi's drowning during a school orientation camp caused a huge public outcry. JOHANNESBURG - The family of Enock Mpianzi wants to sue the Basic Education Department for R10-million. Gauteng Education MEC Panyaza Lesufi says the department received a letter, citing the intention to sue last week. READ: Lesufi receives forensic report into Enock Mpianzi death Mpianzi died during a Parktown Boys' High field trip to the North West. A forensic report into his death was damning for the school, education authorities and the bush camp where he died.